column4: Number eligible for Key Stage 1 assessments3
column5: Percentage achieving at least Level 24 in the following:

column1: 1. Children looked after continuously for at least 12 months as at 31 March excluding those children in respite care. Only children who have been matched to key stage 1 data are included.

2. This is the percentage of children looked after continuously for 12 months at 31 March aged 6 at the start of the academic year who had a valid Unique Pupil Number (UPN) recorded in the SSDA903 return.

3. This is the number of children eligible for key stage 1 assessments. Participation by independent schools is voluntary and therefore only includes results from those independent schools who made a return and which met the statutory standards for assessment and moderation.
4. This is the expected level for the age group. Figures at key stage 1 are based on teacher assessments.
All numbers relating to national or regional totals have been rounded to the nearest 10, all Local Authority numbers have been rounded to the nearest 5.
x = number less than or equal to 5 or percentage where the numerator is less than or equal to 5 or the denominator is less than or equal to 10.
See technical note 18 for more information on rounding and suppression.
